      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index-absolute",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation across 5 VAD operating points — Monte Carlo ensemble",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2023",
      "description": "The hemolysis index (HI) was computed at five VAD operating points (Q = 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 L/min at 2500 RPM) using the modified power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. A 512-sample Monte Carlo ensemble was executed over uncertain boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile ±8%, blood viscosity ±12%, power-law exponent ±5%) to characterise prediction uncertainty. Ensemble mean HI values ranged from 0.0041 to 0.0089, remaining below the clinical threshold of 0.01 at all operating points; 97.3% of ensemble realisations satisfied the threshold. Mesh sensitivity was confirmed across three refinement levels (6.2 M, 14.7 M, and 31.4 M cells); GCI values below 2.1% at all operating points. Experimental HI measurements from the FDA bench study (n=6 replicates per point) were used as the comparator. Normalised root-mean-square error across operating points was 8.4%, within the acceptance band of 15% specified in the credibility plan. The full simulation campaign was executed on the university HPC cluster (SLURM job IDs 4471220–4471731) between 14 March 2024 and 2 April 2024 using OpenFOAM v2312 with the adjoint-corrected sliding-mesh solver. Post-processing was performed in ParaView 5.11 and custom Python scripts (commit a3f9c2d, repository uofa/vad-hemolysis-postproc). Despite this comprehensive experimental and computational campaign, the structured provenance link to the generation Activity has not been recorded in the package metadata."
    }
